analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily focus on establishing or modifying advisory councils and interagency working groups within the federal government. These councils and groups are tasked with providing advice and recommendations to the President and relevant agencies on specific policy areas, such as financial literacy, space policy, Hispanic prosperity, and international regulatory cooperation. The documents also emphasize the importance of collaboration between government agencies, private sector entities, and other stakeholders to achieve the stated policy goals.
title: Federal Advisory Groups and Policy Initiatives
